                --------------------------------------------------------------------

              * Consider the following set_false_path constraint:

                set_false_path -from {u1/Y u2/Y} -to {u3/Y}

                When you specify  reset_path_exception  -from  {u1/Y}  command
                without  the -exact parameter, the command outputs the follow-
                ing:

                set_false_path -from {u2/Y} -to {u3/Y}

                The command reset_path_exception -from {u1/Y}  -exact  outputs
                the following:

                set_false_path -from {u1/Y u2/Y} -to {u3/Y}

                In  this case (when -exact parameter is used), the path excep-
                tion is not reset because differential  matching  is  not  al-
                lowed.

